snippet.textDisplay:
Yes the flu is technically right now more dangerous. But IF this virus start to spread as much or more than the Flu in a pure epidemic. It is a lot worse. Since the Mortality rate seems a lot higher.
The flu with 25 million infections and 10,000 dead is a death ratio of 0.04%. This Corona virus could be 2%. So put that into perspective on mortality rate compared to flu if it starts to spread as wide as the flu does or more.
At 25 million infected it would result in 500,000 deaths. FIVE HUNDRED THOUSAND... Since it is a Novel virus and perhaps a bigger R0 number it could be twice as infectious and 50 million get it with 1 Million dead...
That is frankly nuts.
Sure that means you personally depending on how healthy and "lucky" you are and the level of healthcare you can get your chance could be 98% chance of survival. But that is dependent on several factors.
Like the DR said, good healthcare. But if there is a vast epidemic the hospitals would be overloaded and they couldn't provide things like beds, Oxygen and for worse cases, ventilation. Which would increase your chances of death a lot more..


So that 2% mortality rate is dependent on many factors. How many get infected, how good the healthcare is, how many the healthcare can treat without being overloaded. If it gets overloaded that 2% can become 10%, 15% and higher.. Then you have MILLIONS dying...


That is why I am really worried, because we cannot trust Chinese numbers they provide. Hence why I look a lot at the International cases and mortality rate of those. Because those numbers will be more trustworthy.


Lets also hope things like Rendivir and the other antiviral is effective in vivo and not just in vitro. If it proves in blind study to be effective in vivo it would be tremendous news. It would be able to reduce the disease in an infected person. Allowing the infection spread to be reduced and a time for a potential vaccine to emerge, probably a year later.
